PrecisAcceptance of an Instrument (AMENDMENT OF SURRENDER) wherein the CAMPBELL RIVER BAND further amends the Surrender for Leasing Purposes dated May 22, 1964, with respect to Campbell River Indian Reserve No. 11 in British Columbia, by allowing the Governor in Council to accept any subsequent amendments to the Surrender, or a request to revoke same, upon receipt of a Resolution by the present or any succeeding Band Council.
Attachments
precis:
Acceptance of an Instrument (AMENDMENT OF SURRENDER) wherein the CAMPBELL
RIVER BAND further amends the Surrender for Leasing Purposes dated May 22,
1964, with respect to Campbell River Indian Reserve No. 11 in British
Columbia, by allowing the Governor in Council to accept any subsequent
amendments to the Surrender, or a request to revoke same, upon receipt of a
Resolution by the present or any succeeding Band Council.
